<br>
Friends arrive in our lives.  We spend time together, develop a relationship, become close.  If we've gone through especially emotional times together, then the friendships are that much closer.<br>
<br>
Then things change.  You graduate from school, take a different job, have a baby, whatever it is...  Things change, and we don't see those friends anymore.<br>
<br>
Sometimes we miss them right away, sometimes it's not for weeks or months until we think about them.<br>
<br>
What's different about EQ is that the times are compressed so much.  In RL, it takes months or even years to become close to someone.  In EQ, it seems to just take a couple of weeks.  Going a few days without seeing someone we care about RL isn't usually a big deal, but in EQ, it can be.<br>
<br>
But for many of us, the friends are why we're here.  Shared memories is a big part of that.  The early friendships we made are more valuable to us than the newer ones -- because we become somewhat jaded to what is an amazing game, and that sense of shared amazement is part of what brings us together.<br>
<br>
But there are a lot of really cool people on our server.  If you are receptive to meeting new people, you can surprise yourself.<br>
